vibe: 2.0

meta:
  name: vibe_v2_spec_rewrites
  description: >
    Detailed plan for each spec document rewrite. One section per document
    with current purpose, new purpose, key changes, and rename map.
  session_id: 2026-03-10-a7f3b2
  created_at: "2026-03-10"
  author: claude
  tags:
    - spec
    - documentation
    - migration
    - v2
  status: draft

imports:
  - plans/10_format_spec.vibe
  - plans/20_document_types.vibe
  - plans/60_migration.vibe

context:
  problem: |
    The v1 spec consists of 11 documents oriented around runtime execution.
    The v2 spec must be rewritten to describe a document format for planning,
    not an execution format for runtimes. Each document needs a clear
    rewrite plan specifying what changes, what's preserved, and what the
    target document should cover.

  constraints: |
    - Every v1 spec document must have a disposition (rewrite, delete, or new)
    - Rewritten documents should preserve valuable concepts where possible
    - New documents should fill gaps left by deletions
    - The spec set must be self-consistent (no dangling references)

  assumptions: |
    - Spec documents are Markdown files (not .vibe files)
    - The spec audience is AI systems, tool builders, and format authors
    - Spec documents should be concise and example-heavy

  scope: |
    Covers the content plan for each spec document. Does not contain the
    actual rewritten content (that's the implementation task).

  glossary: |
    - Normative: Spec requirements that consumers MUST follow
    - Informative: Guidance that consumers SHOULD follow
    - Disposition: What happens to a file (rewrite, delete, keep, new)

sections:
  - id: rename_map
    type: specification
    title: Document Rename Map
    content: |
      v1 Document                    -> v2 Document
      -----------------------------------------------
      VIBE_SPEC_v1.md                -> VIBE_SPEC_v2.md
      VIBE_RUNTIME_CONTRACT.md       -> VIBE_CONSUMER_CONTRACT.md
      VIBE_PROGRAM_IR.md             -> VIBE_MERGE_SEMANTICS.md
      VIBE_STEP_TYPES.md             -> VIBE_DOCUMENT_TYPES.md
      VIBE_RUNTIME_HOOKS.md          -> VIBE_INTEGRATION_HOOKS.md
      VIBE_SUBAGENTS.md              -> VIBE_MULTI_AUTHOR.md
      VIBE_REFERENCE_PROGRAM.md      -> VIBE_REFERENCE_DOCUMENT.md
      VIBE_ERRORS.md                 -> VIBE_ERRORS.md (rewrite in place)
      VIBE_SCOPE.md                  -> (merge into spec or delete)
      VIBE_DEPENDENCIES.md           -> VIBE_DEPENDENCIES.md (adapt)
      VIBE_AUTHORING_GUIDE.md        -> VIBE_AUTHORING_GUIDE.md (rewrite)
      VIBE_INDEX.md                  -> VIBE_INDEX.md (rewrite)
      (new)                          -> VIBE_MCP_SERVER.md

  - id: spec_v2
    type: specification
    title: "VIBE_SPEC_v2.md (rewrite of VIBE_SPEC_v1.md)"
    depends_on:
      - rename_map
    content: |
      Current purpose: Language overview defining program model, file format,
      top-level fields, standard library, and philosophy.

      New purpose: Document format overview defining the .vibe format,
      top-level fields, and design philosophy.

      Key changes:
      - Program model (parse->compile->plan->apply->validate) replaced with
        document model (write->validate->review->import)
      - Remove: tools, workflow, validation field definitions
      - Add: sections, decisions, quality field definitions
      - Update: meta (new fields), artifacts (new fields), context (new fields)
      - Remove: legacy fields section entirely
      - Update: standard library description (quality.vibe, templates)
      - Update: philosophy (document format, not execution format)
      - Update: related documents list

      Structure:
      1. Format overview (what .vibe files are)
      2. Document model (write -> validate -> review -> import)
      3. File format (YAML, version declaration)
      4. Top-level fields (all 8 fields defined)
      5. Standard library reference
      6. Related documents
      7. Philosophy

  - id: consumer_contract
    type: specification
    title: "VIBE_CONSUMER_CONTRACT.md (replaces VIBE_RUNTIME_CONTRACT.md)"
    depends_on:
      - rename_map
    content: |
      Current purpose: Required runtime behaviors -- parsing, merge rules,
      plan/apply phases, tool-truth, gates, retries, evidence, security.

      New purpose: Required consumer behaviors -- how tools, AI systems,
      and humans should parse, validate, and interpret .vibe documents.

      Key changes:
      - Remove: plan/apply phase requirements
      - Remove: tool execution requirements
      - Remove: gate evaluation requirements
      - Remove: retry policy requirements
      - Remove: evidence collection requirements
      - Keep (adapted): parsing requirements (YAML parsing rules)
      - Keep (adapted): merge rules (simplified for v2)
      - Keep (adapted): security considerations (path traversal in imports)
      - Add: field interpretation rules (how to read sections, decisions)
      - Add: validation requirements (schema validation behavior)
      - Add: status field semantics (draft/review/final lifecycle)

      Structure:
      1. What is a consumer? (definition and examples)
      2. Parsing requirements (YAML, version check)
      3. Import resolution (path resolution, circular detection)
      4. Merge behavior (field-by-field merge rules)
      5. Field interpretation (how to read each field)
      6. Validation (schema validation expectations)
      7. Security (import path safety)

  - id: merge_semantics
    type: specification
    title: "VIBE_MERGE_SEMANTICS.md (replaces VIBE_PROGRAM_IR.md)"
    depends_on:
      - rename_map
    content: |
      Current purpose: Canonical compiled/merged representation (Program IR)
      that runtimes produce deterministically from import resolution.

      New purpose: Simplified merge rules for combining imported .vibe files.
      No compilation step, no IR, just straightforward field merging.

      Key changes:
      - Remove: Program IR concept entirely
      - Remove: Tool merging (tools field removed)
      - Remove: Workflow step merging (workflow field removed)
      - Remove: Validation merging (validation field removed)
      - Simplify: Field-level merge rules only
      - Add: Conflict resolution examples

      Structure:
      1. Import resolution algorithm
      2. Circular import detection
      3. Field merge rules (one rule per field)
      4. Conflict resolution (what happens on duplicate IDs)
      5. Examples (two files merged, showing result)

      Merge rules (from 10_format_spec.vibe):
      - vibe: root wins
      - meta: root wins (no deep merge)
      - imports: already resolved, not merged
      - context: deep merge, root keys override
      - artifacts: concat, deduplicate by path (root wins)
      - sections: concat (root after imports)
      - decisions: concat, deduplicate by id (root wins)
      - quality: concat, deduplicate by id (root wins)

  - id: document_types
    type: specification
    title: "VIBE_DOCUMENT_TYPES.md (replaces VIBE_STEP_TYPES.md)"
    depends_on:
      - rename_map
    content: |
      Current purpose: Step type definitions (plan, generate, apply,
      validate, summarize) with suggested runtime defaults.

      New purpose: Section type definitions and document archetypes.

      Key changes:
      - Remove: All step type definitions
      - Add: Six section types (analysis, design, decision, specification,
        risk, checklist) with definitions and examples
      - Add: Document archetypes (overview, architecture, implementation
        plan, risk assessment, ADR collection)
      - Add: Quality criteria types (review, test, metric, checklist)
      - Based entirely on 20_document_types.vibe

      Structure:
      1. Section types (definition, use cases, examples for each)
      2. Document archetypes (purpose, typical sections, examples)
      3. Quality criteria types (definition, use cases for each)
      4. Extensibility model

  - id: integration_hooks
    type: specification
    title: "VIBE_INTEGRATION_HOOKS.md (replaces VIBE_RUNTIME_HOOKS.md)"
    depends_on:
      - rename_map
    content: |
      Current purpose: Runtime hook extensibility -- pre/post step hooks,
      gate hooks, custom event handlers.

      New purpose: How external tools integrate with .vibe files without
      executing them.

      Key changes:
      - Remove: Pre/post step hooks (no steps)
      - Remove: Gate hooks (no gates)
      - Remove: Custom event handlers (no events)
      - Add: MCP integration (how AI tools use the MCP server)
      - Add: IDE integration (syntax highlighting, preview, navigation)
      - Add: CI/CD integration (validating .vibe files in pipelines)
      - Add: Import hooks (custom import resolvers)

      Structure:
      1. MCP integration (tools, prompts, resources)
      2. IDE integration (language support, preview rendering)
      3. CI/CD integration (validation in pipelines, diff tracking)
      4. Custom import resolvers
      5. Ecosystem conventions

  - id: multi_author
    type: specification
    title: "VIBE_MULTI_AUTHOR.md (replaces VIBE_SUBAGENTS.md)"
    depends_on:
      - rename_map
    content: |
      Current purpose: Subagent delegation patterns for multi-agent
      workflows and parallel execution.

      New purpose: Multi-author patterns for .vibe documents. How
      multiple AI systems and humans collaborate on planning documents.

      Key changes:
      - Remove: Runtime delegation patterns
      - Remove: Parallel execution coordination
      - Add: Author tracking via meta.author field
      - Add: Session-based collaboration (multiple authors in one session)
      - Add: Cross-session reference patterns
      - Add: Review and approval workflows (draft -> review -> final)
      - Add: Conflict resolution for concurrent edits

      Structure:
      1. Author identification (meta.author values and conventions)
      2. Session collaboration (multiple authors, one session)
      3. Cross-session building (importing from prior sessions)
      4. Review workflows (status field lifecycle)
      5. Conflict resolution (what happens when two authors edit)

  - id: reference_document
    type: specification
    title: "VIBE_REFERENCE_DOCUMENT.md (replaces VIBE_REFERENCE_PROGRAM.md)"
    depends_on:
      - rename_map
    content: |
      Current purpose: Canonical example v1 program with workflow steps,
      plan manifest, and runtime behavior.

      New purpose: Canonical example v2 document showing a realistic
      planning scenario with all v2 features.

      Key changes:
      - Replace: Execution example with planning document example
      - Replace: Plan manifest example with quality criteria example
      - Replace: Runtime behavior with document lifecycle
      - Keep (adapted): Repository layout (updated for v2)
      - Show: A realistic planning scenario (e.g., planning an API feature)

      Structure:
      1. Purpose of the reference document
      2. Reference repository layout (v2)
      3. Reference .vibe document (complete example)
      4. Section examples (one of each type)
      5. Decision examples (with full ADR structure)
      6. Quality criteria examples
      7. Import example (composing documents)
      8. Document lifecycle (draft -> review -> final)

  - id: errors_rewrite
    type: specification
    title: "VIBE_ERRORS.md (rewrite in place)"
    depends_on:
      - rename_map
    content: |
      Current purpose: Runtime error taxonomy and codes covering parse
      errors, merge errors, execution errors, tool errors, gate errors.

      New purpose: Document validation error taxonomy covering parse
      errors, schema errors, import resolution errors.

      Key changes:
      - Keep: Parse error codes (YAML syntax errors)
      - Keep (adapted): Merge error codes (import conflicts)
      - Remove: Execution error codes (no execution)
      - Remove: Tool error codes (no tools)
      - Remove: Gate error codes (no gates)
      - Add: Schema validation error codes
      - Add: Import resolution error codes
      - Add: MCP server error codes

      Error categories:
      1. PARSE_* -- YAML parsing failures
      2. SCHEMA_* -- Schema validation failures
      3. IMPORT_* -- Import resolution failures
      4. MERGE_* -- Field merge conflicts
      5. MCP_* -- MCP server operation errors

  - id: scope_disposition
    type: decision
    title: "VIBE_SCOPE.md Disposition"
    content: |
      VIBE_SCOPE.md defines repository write scope rules. In v1 this
      controlled which paths the runtime could write to. In v2 there
      is no runtime writing files.

      Options:
      1. Delete entirely -- write scope is a runtime concern
      2. Merge into VIBE_SPEC_v2.md as a note about scope field
      3. Rewrite as document scope guidance (what artifacts should cover)

      Recommendation: Delete. The scope concept was about constraining
      runtime side effects. Without a runtime, there's nothing to scope.
      If artifact path guidance is needed, it belongs in the authoring guide.

  - id: dependencies_adapt
    type: specification
    title: "VIBE_DEPENDENCIES.md (adapt)"
    depends_on:
      - rename_map
    content: |
      Current purpose: Artifact dependency semantics for execution-time
      dependency resolution.

      New purpose: Artifact dependency semantics for design-time
      planning. How artifacts reference each other and how depends_on
      fields are interpreted.

      Key changes:
      - Remove: Execution-time resolution (build ordering, etc.)
      - Keep: depends_on field semantics
      - Keep: Dependency graph concepts
      - Add: Section depends_on semantics
      - Add: Cross-document dependency via imports

      Structure:
      1. Artifact depends_on (what it means for artifacts to depend)
      2. Section depends_on (content ordering within a document)
      3. Cross-document dependencies (via imports)
      4. Circular dependency detection

  - id: authoring_guide_rewrite
    type: specification
    title: "VIBE_AUTHORING_GUIDE.md (rewrite)"
    depends_on:
      - rename_map
    content: |
      Current purpose: Guide for writing v1 programs (plan first,
      manifest, gates, small steps).

      New purpose: Guide for writing v2 documents (section types,
      decisions, quality criteria, MCP workflow).

      Key changes:
      - Replace: "Golden Rules" (v1 execution focused) with new
        authoring principles for document creation
      - Replace: Step writing guidance with section writing guidance
      - Replace: Gate guidance with quality criteria guidance
      - Replace: Plan manifest guidance with decision documentation
      - Add: Using the MCP server for document creation
      - Add: Template usage guidance
      - Add: Session management best practices
      - Keep: Artifact writing guidance (adapted for v2 fields)

      New golden rules (proposed):
      1. Start with context (problem, constraints, assumptions)
      2. Use the right section type for each piece of content
      3. Make decisions explicit (use the decisions field)
      4. Define quality criteria (what does "done" look like)
      5. Compose via imports (don't repeat, reference)
      6. Track status (draft -> review -> final)

  - id: index_rewrite
    type: specification
    title: "VIBE_INDEX.md (rewrite)"
    depends_on:
      - rename_map
    content: |
      Current purpose: Index of v1 spec documents with normative vs
      recommended categorization.

      New purpose: Index of v2 spec documents.

      Key changes:
      - Update: Document list to v2 names
      - Update: Categorization (normative vs informative)
      - Update: Standard library description
      - Update: Completeness checklist for v2
      - Add: MCP server documentation reference

      v2 Normative documents:
      - VIBE_SPEC_v2.md
      - VIBE_CONSUMER_CONTRACT.md
      - VIBE_MERGE_SEMANTICS.md
      - VIBE_ERRORS.md

      v2 Informative documents:
      - VIBE_DOCUMENT_TYPES.md
      - VIBE_DEPENDENCIES.md
      - VIBE_AUTHORING_GUIDE.md
      - VIBE_REFERENCE_DOCUMENT.md
      - VIBE_INTEGRATION_HOOKS.md
      - VIBE_MULTI_AUTHOR.md
      - VIBE_MCP_SERVER.md

  - id: mcp_server_doc
    type: specification
    title: "VIBE_MCP_SERVER.md (new)"
    content: |
      No v1 equivalent. New document.

      Purpose: MCP server specification and reference. Defines the
      tools, prompts, and resources the server exposes.

      Based on: 40_mcp_server.vibe and 50_session_system.vibe

      Structure:
      1. Overview (what the MCP server does)
      2. Setup (Docker, configuration)
      3. Tools reference (one section per tool with params and returns)
      4. Prompts reference (plan_in_vibe)
      5. Resources reference (spec, templates, quality)
      6. Session management (ID format, lifecycle, storage)
      7. Error handling (error codes and messages)

decisions:
  - id: dec_scope_disposition
    title: Delete VIBE_SCOPE.md rather than rewrite
    status: proposed
    context: |
      VIBE_SCOPE.md is entirely about runtime write scope constraints.
      In v2 there is no runtime to constrain.
    options:
      - name: delete
        description: Remove entirely, scope is a runtime concept
      - name: rewrite
        description: Rewrite as document scope guidance
      - name: merge
        description: Merge relevant bits into VIBE_SPEC_v2.md
    chosen: delete
    rationale: |
      The concept of "scope" in v1 means "which filesystem paths the
      runtime may write to." Without a runtime, this has no meaning.
      Any guidance about artifact paths belongs in the authoring guide,
      not a dedicated scope document.
    consequences:
      - One fewer spec document
      - No dedicated scope documentation
      - Artifact path guidance in authoring guide if needed

  - id: dec_rename_convention
    title: Use descriptive names that reflect v2 concepts
    status: proposed
    context: |
      Should renamed spec documents keep similar names or adopt
      entirely new names that reflect v2 concepts?
    options:
      - name: keep_names
        description: Keep names like RUNTIME_CONTRACT, just update content
      - name: rename_descriptive
        description: Rename to match v2 concepts (CONSUMER_CONTRACT, etc.)
    chosen: rename_descriptive
    rationale: |
      Names like RUNTIME_CONTRACT are misleading in a format without
      a runtime. Descriptive renames (CONSUMER_CONTRACT, MERGE_SEMANTICS,
      DOCUMENT_TYPES) immediately communicate the v2 focus. Git tracks
      the rename history.
    consequences:
      - All cross-references must be updated
      - Git history shows renames
      - New names are self-documenting

quality:
  - id: q_every_doc_planned
    type: checklist
    description: Every spec document has a rewrite plan
    criteria: |
      - All 11 existing spec documents have a disposition
      - All 5 new spec documents have content plans
      - No spec document is unaccounted for

  - id: q_no_dangling_refs
    type: review
    description: Planned spec set has no dangling references
    criteria: |
      - Every cross-reference between planned docs is valid
      - No planned doc references a doc that will be deleted
      - Index document lists all planned docs

  - id: q_sufficient_detail
    type: review
    description: Rewrite plans have enough detail to execute
    criteria: |
      - Each rewrite plan specifies current purpose and new purpose
      - Key changes are enumerated
      - Target document structure is outlined
      - Enough detail for an AI to write the actual document
